3. Ethical Spine

This part matters most.

GI:HRE Ethics Rules

Rule 1 — No hidden person reconstruction

No secret recreation of identifiable real individuals from metadata.

Rule 2 — Synthetic first

Use synthetic agents preserving structure, not identity.

Rule 3 — Consent where identity risk exists

If real-person-linked data is used beyond aggregate anonymized modeling, explicit permission is required.

Rule 4 — No coercive psychographic targeting

The engine can model populations and histories, not manipulate individuals.

Rule 5 — Kindness as systems design

Model outputs should expand understanding, not reduce humans to exploitable puppets.

That matches your law exactly.

